# Pattern: public landing page + protected content

A members-only site usually wants two things that pull in opposite directions:

1. the actual content must be **protected** (only logged-in members see it);
2. links to the site shared in chats/social must still produce a **nice link
   preview** (title, description, image).

If oauth2-proxy protects `/`, then any link to the site previews as the login
page (or nothing) — every share looks broken. The fix: a small **public
teaser** at `/` with proper Open Graph metadata, and the real content on
**protected** paths.

## Shape

```
/                 → public teaser page: <title>, OG meta, an OG image, a
                    "Members, sign in" link. NO real content.
/_astro/...       → public static assets the teaser needs (CSS/JS/fonts)
/favicon.ico      → public
/og-image.png     → public (referenced by the OG meta)
/<everything-else>→ PROTECTED: the real members-only content
```

The teaser page carries the link-preview metadata:

```html
<meta property="og:title"       content="{{ community_name }}" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Members area of {{ community_name }}" />
<meta property="og:image"       content="https://{{ domain }}/og-image.png" />
<meta property="og:url"         content="https://{{ domain }}/" />
```

## Let only the teaser + its assets through oauth2-proxy

Use oauth2-proxy `--skip-auth-route` to bypass auth for exactly the public
surface — the teaser, its static assets, the favicon and the OG image —
everything else stays protected:

```
--skip-auth-route=^/$
--skip-auth-route=^/_astro/
--skip-auth-route=^/favicon
--skip-auth-route=^/og-image\.png$
```

(`--skip-auth-route` takes a regex and may be repeated. Keep the public set as
tight as possible — anything not matched requires login.)

## Result

- A crawler/unfurler fetching `https://{{ domain }}/` gets the teaser with full
  OG tags → clean link previews everywhere.
- A member following any deeper link hits a protected path → oauth2-proxy sends
  them through the central IdP, then serves the real content.
- No protected data is ever reachable without auth.

